//====================================================================
// SHARED MATH UTILITIES (Sprint 2.3 - Tier 1)
//
// Pure, swing-agnostic math primitives. These functions know nothing
// about swings, the Swing Database, or engine state - they operate
// only on the values passed to them as parameters. This is what makes
// them reusable by any future module (BOS, CHoCH, Liquidity, Order
// Blocks, FVG), not just the Swing Strength system built on top of
// them in later patches of this sprint.
//
// Tier 1 must NEVER:
//   - access the Swing Database
//   - access arrays of any kind
//   - access swing IDs
//   - access engine state (activePendingSwingType, activeTransitionSwingId, etc.)
//   - access Candidate Detection
//   - access Replacement Logic
//   - access Confirmation Logic
//   - access Visualization
//
// Tier 1 must always remain:
//   - Pure: output depends only on the values passed in as parameters
//   - Deterministic: same inputs always produce the same output
//   - Stateless: no var/global state read or written
//   - Replay safe: no series/bar-context dependency of any kind
//   - Reusable by any future module, not just Swing Strength
//   - Free of runtime errors on zero, na, or otherwise degenerate inputs
//
// This section intentionally contains NO Swing Strength logic, NO
// normalization/saturation curves, and NO calls into the database.
// That begins in a later patch.
//====================================================================

// safeDivide - the single shared guard against division-by-zero and
// na-denominator across every ratio/velocity primitive below.
//
// fallbackValue defaults to na, preserving the original behaviour for
// every existing caller in this file without any call-site changes -
// "undefined" stays honestly represented as na unless a caller
// explicitly decides otherwise. That decision deliberately belongs to
// the caller (Tier 2, or a future module), never to this function -
// safeDivide itself still makes no modeling assumptions of its own.
safeDivide(float numerator, float denominator, float fallbackValue = na) =>
    float result = fallbackValue

    if not na(denominator) and denominator != 0
        result := numerator / denominator

    result

// deriveDistance - absolute price distance between two levels.
// No division involved, so no zero-denominator edge case exists here.
// na inputs propagate na naturally through math.abs(), which is
// already safe (does not error on na).
deriveDistance(float priceA, float priceB) =>
    math.abs(priceA - priceB)

// deriveBarsElapsed - absolute bar separation between two bar indices.
// Centralizes trivial-but-ubiquitous arithmetic that every future
// module (Strength, BOS timing, OB formation windows, FVG age) would
// otherwise reimplement independently. No division, no na/zero edge
// case beyond standard na propagation through math.abs().
deriveBarsElapsed(int barA, int barB) =>
    math.abs(barA - barB)

// deriveVelocity - price distance per bar elapsed. Guards barsElapsed
// == 0 (and na) via safeDivide, rather than dividing directly - this
// is a real edge case, not a hypothetical one: a swing formed and
// confirmed within a single bar of separation would otherwise divide
// by zero.
deriveVelocity(float distance, int barsElapsed) =>
    safeDivide(distance, barsElapsed)

// deriveBodyDominanceRatio - how much of the candle's range the body
// occupies. Guards candleRange == 0 (a doji-shaped or zero-range
// pivot candle) via safeDivide. Bounded [0,1] under normal inputs by
// construction of its callers (body length can never exceed range) -
// this function does not itself clamp, since clamping is a modeling
// decision, not a math-primitive concern, and is out of scope here.
deriveBodyDominanceRatio(float bodyLength, float candleRange) =>
    safeDivide(bodyLength, candleRange)

// deriveWickRejectionRatio - how much of the candle's range is wick
// beyond the body at the extreme. Same zero-range guard, same
// no-clamping rationale as deriveBodyDominanceRatio above.
deriveWickRejectionRatio(float extremeWick, float candleRange) =>
    safeDivide(extremeWick, candleRange)

