//====================================================================
// SWING STRENGTH SYSTEM (Sprint 2.3 - Tier 2: Normalized Scores)
//
// Relocated here in Patch 4 (was previously between MINIMUM LEG
// FILTER and REPLACEMENT ENGINE). This move is mechanical, not a
// design change: computeSwingStrength() (Tier 3, added below) must be
// database-lookup-free per the approved Patch 4 wiring policy, which
// makes it - like Tier 1 and Tier 2 - pure and swing-agnostic in the
// sense of touching no array/database state. That means it has no
// dependency on anything in ENGINE API, and ENGINE API's
// finalizeConfirmedSwing() now needs to call it - so this whole
// section must be defined before ENGINE API, satisfying Pine's
// define-before-use requirement. No function body in this relocated
// section was altered by the move.
//
// This section is Strength-specific and calibrated - unlike Tier 1
// (SHARED MATH UTILITIES), which is deliberately opinion-free, Tier 2
// "owns" Strength's specific interpretation of what a good leg,
// efficient move, or clean rejection candle looks like, via the named
// calibration constants below.
//
// A future module wanting its own interpretation of the same raw
// measurement (e.g. a different displacement threshold for Order
// Blocks) applies its own saturation curve to Tier 1's raw output
// directly - it does NOT reuse these functions or these constants.
//
// Tier 2 must NEVER:
//   - access the Swing Database
//   - access swing IDs
//   - access engine state
//   - write to any database field
//   - compute a composite score (that is Tier 3, below)
//
// Tier 2 must always remain:
//   - Deterministic, replay safe, non-repainting
//   - Built only from Tier 1 primitives - no unguarded division
//   - Bounded [0.0, 1.0] whenever its inputs are defined and satisfy
//     their documented (non-negative) contract
//   - Explicit (na) when an input is undefined, never a fabricated
//     fallback number
//
// Calibration Policy: the constants below are Calibration Version 1 -
// approved engineering baselines, not empirically optimized values.
// They may be revised only through a dedicated calibration review
// (per project Calibration Policy), never as part of an architecture
// change.
//====================================================================

// Saturation constants - control how quickly each ratio-based score
// approaches 1.0. Each K is the input value at which its score equals
// exactly 0.5 (the saturation curve's inflection reference point).
STRENGTH_LEG_DISTANCE_SATURATION_K = 3.0     // a 3x-ATR leg scores 0.5
STRENGTH_LEG_EFFICIENCY_SATURATION_K = 0.30  // a 0.3 ATR/bar velocity scores 0.5

// Candle Structure component weights - must sum to 1.0 for
// normalizeCandleStructureScore's convex-combination bound to hold.
STRENGTH_CANDLE_WICK_COMPONENT_WEIGHT = 0.60
STRENGTH_CANDLE_BODY_COMPONENT_WEIGHT = 0.40

// normalizeLegDistanceScore
// -------------------------
// raw ratio = legDistance / formationATR        (ATR-multiples of leg size)
// score     = ratio / (ratio + K)                (saturating curve)
//
// Proof this is bounded [0,1] whenever the inputs are defined and
// legDistance >= 0, formationATR > 0 (both hold by construction of
// their upstream sources - deriveDistance() and swingFormationATR,
// an ATR reading, are never negative):
//   - ratio = legDistance / formationATR >= 0, since a non-negative
//     numerator divided by a positive denominator is non-negative.
//   - K (STRENGTH_LEG_DISTANCE_SATURATION_K) is a fixed positive
//     constant (3.0), so (ratio + K) > 0 always - strictly greater
//     than zero, never merely non-negative. This is what makes the
//     final division safe without needing to special-case ratio == 0.
//   - Lower bound: ratio == 0 => score = 0 / (0 + K) = 0.
//   - Upper bound: as ratio -> infinity, ratio / (ratio + K) -> 1,
//     but never reaches or exceeds 1, since ratio < ratio + K for any
//     K > 0. The score is therefore always strictly < 1, asymptotic
//     rather than clipped - no explicit clamp is required to enforce
//     the upper bound; it is a structural property of the formula.
//
// Proof of monotonicity (larger legDistance never produces a smaller
// score): let f(r) = r / (r + K). Its derivative with respect to r is
// f'(r) = K / (r + K)^2, which is strictly positive for all r >= 0
// and K > 0 (a positive constant divided by a square, which is always
// positive). A strictly positive derivative means f is strictly
// increasing - a larger raw ratio can never produce an equal or
// smaller score. This holds independent of the specific K value
// chosen, which is why recalibrating K (Calibration Policy) can
// change the score's steepness without ever breaking monotonicity.
//
// If formationATR is na or 0, safeDivide's guard returns na for
// ratio, and na propagates through the second safeDivide call
// (denominator na is caught by its own guard) - the function returns
// na explicitly rather than a fabricated number, exactly matching the
// "undefined stays explicit" requirement.
normalizeLegDistanceScore(float legDistance, float formationATR) =>
    float ratio = safeDivide(legDistance, formationATR)
    safeDivide(ratio, ratio + STRENGTH_LEG_DISTANCE_SATURATION_K)

// normalizeLegEfficiencyScore
// ---------------------------
// Identical saturating shape and identical proof structure to
// normalizeLegDistanceScore above, applied to velocity instead of
// raw distance: raw ratio = legVelocity / formationATR (ATR-multiples
// of speed per bar), saturated the same way with its own K
// (STRENGTH_LEG_EFFICIENCY_SATURATION_K). Bounded-[0,1] and
// monotonicity proofs are identical by substitution - both rely only
// on K being a fixed positive constant and the numerator being
// non-negative by construction (legVelocity is a distance-per-bar
// derived from deriveVelocity(), which is never negative given
// deriveDistance()'s and deriveBarsElapsed()'s non-negative outputs).
normalizeLegEfficiencyScore(float legVelocity, float formationATR) =>
    float ratio = safeDivide(legVelocity, formationATR)
    safeDivide(ratio, ratio + STRENGTH_LEG_EFFICIENCY_SATURATION_K)

// normalizeCandleStructureScore
// ------------------------------
// score = (wickRatio * WICK_WEIGHT) + (bodyRatio * BODY_WEIGHT)
//
// This is a convex combination, not a saturation curve - both inputs
// arrive already bounded [0,1] (Tier 1's deriveWickRejectionRatio()
// and deriveBodyDominanceRatio() guarantee this whenever candleRange
// > 0, since a wick or body length can never exceed the candle's own
// range by construction of how they are measured in
// captureFormationSnapshot()).
//
// Proof this is bounded [0,1]: for any convex combination
// w1*x1 + w2*x2 where x1, x2 in [0,1], w1 >= 0, w2 >= 0, and
// w1 + w2 == 1:
//   - Minimum: both weights are non-negative and both inputs are
//     bounded below by 0, so the sum can never go below
//     0*w1 + 0*w2 = 0.
//   - Maximum: since w1 + w2 == 1, the maximum possible value of the
//     sum is achieved when both x1 and x2 equal their upper bound of
//     1, giving 1*w1 + 1*w2 = w1 + w2 = 1. No input combination can
//     exceed this, because increasing either x_i beyond 1 is outside
//     its documented contract - the bound holds precisely because
//     both inputs satisfy [0,1], not because this function clamps.
// This is why "no clamping is required if the inputs satisfy their
// documented bounds" is a provable statement here, not an assumption:
// the [0,1] output range is a direct algebraic consequence of the
// [0,1] input range and the weights summing to exactly 1.0 - remove
// either precondition and the guarantee no longer holds.
//
// Monotonicity: the partial derivative with respect to either input
// is simply its own fixed weight (a positive constant), so the score
// is monotonically non-decreasing in both wickRatio and bodyRatio
// independently - a stronger, more directly evident property here
// than in the saturation functions above, since the relationship is
// linear rather than asymptotic.
//
// If either input is na (Tier 1's zero-candle-range guard), na
// propagates through both the multiplication and the addition -
// consistent with the "explicit na, never fabricated" requirement.
//
// Weight-sum integrity: mirrors the top-level Strength weight-sum
// safeguard below (Tier 3) - gated behind Developer Mode, same
// documented limitation as that check, pending Sprint 2.8's Engine
// Integrity System.
normalizeCandleStructureScore(float wickRatio, float bodyRatio) =>
    debugAssert(math.abs((STRENGTH_CANDLE_WICK_COMPONENT_WEIGHT + STRENGTH_CANDLE_BODY_COMPONENT_WEIGHT) - 1.0) < 0.0001, "Candle Structure component weights must sum to 1.0.")

    (wickRatio * STRENGTH_CANDLE_WICK_COMPONENT_WEIGHT) + (bodyRatio * STRENGTH_CANDLE_BODY_COMPONENT_WEIGHT)

//--------------------------------------------------------------------
// TIER 3 - COMPOSITE (Sprint 2.3 - Patch 4)
//
// Composite weights - Calibration Version 1, frozen. 40% Leg
// Distance, 30% Leg Efficiency, 30% Candle Structure. Future changes
// require a formal calibration review (Calibration Policy) - never an
// ad-hoc edit here.
//--------------------------------------------------------------------

STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_DISTANCE = 0.40
STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_EFFICIENCY = 0.30
STRENGTH_WEIGHT_CANDLE_STRUCTURE = 0.30

// computeSwingStrength
// ---------------------
// The Tier 1 -> Tier 2 -> Tier 3 orchestrator for a single swing's
// Strength. Deliberately takes every needed value as an explicit
// parameter and performs ZERO database lookups internally, per the
// approved Patch 4 wiring policy - this function is pure, exactly
// like Tier 1 and Tier 2, even though it is Strength-specific.
// Gathering the raw values from the database is the caller's
// responsibility (finalizeConfirmedSwing(), below in ENGINE API).
//
// First Confirmed Swing (Question 3, frozen decision): if no previous
// confirmed swing exists, there is no valid reference to measure this
// swing's leg against. Returns na explicitly - no synthetic
// reference, no default score.
//
// Missing Data Policy (Question 4, frozen decision): full na
// propagation. If any one of the three Tier 2 scores is na (e.g. a
// zero-range pivot candle, or formationATR still na during ATR
// warm-up), the composite is na - not renormalized among the
// remaining components, not substituted. Pine's native na arithmetic
// already enforces this without extra branching: na multiplied by a
// weight is na, and na added to any value is na, so the single
// weighted-sum expression below is correct by construction whenever
// any component is na - no explicit na-checking branch is needed
// beyond the first-confirmed-swing guard.
//
// Historical Immutability (Question 5, frozen decision): this
// function is called exactly once per swing, from
// finalizeConfirmedSwing(), which itself is only ever called once per
// swing (at confirmation). Nothing in this codebase calls
// computeSwingStrength() a second time for an already-confirmed
// swing - the stored result is permanent by construction of its
// single call site, not by a runtime guard.
computeSwingStrength(bool previousConfirmedExists, float previousConfirmedPrice, int previousConfirmedBar, float thisPrice, int thisBar, float formationATR, float candleRange, float candleBody, float candleExtremeWick) =>
    debugAssert(math.abs((STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_DISTANCE + STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_EFFICIENCY + STRENGTH_WEIGHT_CANDLE_STRUCTURE) - 1.0) < 0.0001, "Swing Strength composite weights must sum to 1.0.")

    float strength = na

    if previousConfirmedExists
        float legDistance = deriveDistance(thisPrice, previousConfirmedPrice)
        int barsElapsed = deriveBarsElapsed(thisBar, previousConfirmedBar)
        float legVelocity = deriveVelocity(legDistance, barsElapsed)

        float wickRatio = deriveWickRejectionRatio(candleExtremeWick, candleRange)
        float bodyRatio = deriveBodyDominanceRatio(candleBody, candleRange)

        float distanceScore = normalizeLegDistanceScore(legDistance, formationATR)
        float efficiencyScore = normalizeLegEfficiencyScore(legVelocity, formationATR)
        float candleScore = normalizeCandleStructureScore(wickRatio, bodyRatio)

        strength := (distanceScore * STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_DISTANCE) + (efficiencyScore * STRENGTH_WEIGHT_LEG_EFFICIENCY) + (candleScore * STRENGTH_WEIGHT_CANDLE_STRUCTURE)

    strength

//====================================================================
// ENGINE API
//====================================================================

startPendingSwing(int swingId, int swingType, float swingPrice, int swingBar) =>
    createSwing(swingId, swingType, swingPrice, swingBar)

confirmPendingSwing(int swingId) =>
    bool updated = updateSwingStatus(swingId, STATUS_CONFIRMED)
    validateDatabaseInDebug("Database integrity failed after confirmation.")
    updated

// finalizeConfirmedSwing - the single approved extension point for
// confirmation-time metadata (mirrors captureFormationSnapshot()'s role
// as the sole extension point for formation-time metadata). Called by
// the Replacement Engine exactly once, immediately after a swing has
// been successfully confirmed - never before, never more than once per
// swing, consistent with "Swing Strength is calculated exactly once."
//
// Patch 4: now also computes and writes swingStrength. This is the
// one function in the Strength pipeline allowed to touch the
// database - it gathers this swing's own stored formation fields via
// the read-only accessors, plus the previousConfirmed* reference
// passed in explicitly by the caller (captured before this swing's
// own status flipped to CONFIRMED - see processSameSideCandidate()/
// processOppositeCandidate() for the ordering fix), then hands fully
// resolved values to computeSwingStrength(), which itself performs no
// database access at all (approved Patch 4 wiring policy).
//
// Future patches extend this function body only - Swing Importance,
// Structure Label, and any other confirmation-time field all get
// added here, not scattered back into the Replacement Engine. (Note:
// BOS/CHoCH/Liquidity-Sweep fields do NOT belong here - those are
// post-confirmation events requiring their own future extension
// point, per the Sprint 2.3 architecture review.)
finalizeConfirmedSwing(int swingId, float atrValue, float previousConfirmedPrice, int previousConfirmedBar, bool previousConfirmedExists) =>
    setSwingATR(swingId, atrValue)

    [_, thisPrice, thisBar, _, _] = getSwing(swingId)
    [formationATR, _] = getSwingFormationATR(swingId)
    [candleRange, _] = getSwingCandleRange(swingId)
    [candleBody, _] = getSwingCandleBody(swingId)
    [candleExtremeWick, _] = getSwingCandleExtremeWick(swingId)

    float strength = computeSwingStrength(previousConfirmedExists, previousConfirmedPrice, previousConfirmedBar, thisPrice, thisBar, formationATR, candleRange, candleBody, candleExtremeWick)

    setSwingStrength(swingId, strength)

replacePendingSwing(int swingId, float replacementPrice, int replacementBar) =>
    int swingIndex = swingIndexFromId(swingId)
    bool exists = swingIndex != NO_INDEX

    if exists
        array.set(swingPrices, swingIndex, replacementPrice)
        array.set(swingBars, swingIndex, replacementBar)
        array.set(swingStatuses, swingIndex, STATUS_PENDING)

        // Sprint 2.3: formation data tracks the replacement, not the
        // original candidate - by the time this swing is confirmed, "the
        // swing" IS the replaced version, mirroring how price/bar already
        // update here rather than staying anchored to the first candidate.
        captureFormationSnapshot(swingId)

    validateDatabaseInDebug("Database integrity failed after replacement.")
    exists

rejectPendingSwing(int swingId) =>
    bool exists = swingIndexFromId(swingId) != NO_INDEX
    debugAssert(exists, "Rejected swing references a missing active swing.")
    exists

archivePendingSwing(int swingId) =>
    bool updated = updateSwingStatus(swingId, STATUS_REJECTED)
    validateDatabaseInDebug("Database integrity failed after archive.")
    updated

getActiveSwing(int swingId) =>
    getSwing(swingId)

getLastConfirmedSwing() =>
    databaseLastConfirmedSwing()

//====================================================================
// MINIMUM LEG FILTER
// Evaluates the transition swing against the last confirmed swing.
// Same-side replacement candidates are never blocked by this filter.
//
// Sprint 2.2: the filter's comparison logic (Distance >= Threshold)
// is unchanged. It no longer knows or cares how the threshold is
// produced - that responsibility is fully delegated to
// resolveMinimumLegThreshold() below (Option B - dedicated Threshold
// Provider, per approved design).
//====================================================================

legDistance(float transitionSwingPrice, float confirmedSwingPrice) =>
    math.abs(transitionSwingPrice - confirmedSwingPrice)

// Threshold Provider (Sprint 2.2)
// Resolves the active Minimum Leg threshold based on thresholdMode.
// This is the ONLY place that knows about Fixed / Adaptive ATR / Manual
// Override. passesMinimumLegFilter() only ever sees the resulting float.
resolveMinimumLegThreshold() =>
    float threshold = minimumLegPoints

    if thresholdMode == THRESHOLD_MANUAL_OVERRIDE
        // Dev/Test only - ignores Fixed and Adaptive ATR entirely, per
        // approved design. Not intended for production trading use.
        threshold := manualLegPoints
    else if thresholdMode == THRESHOLD_ADAPTIVE_ATR
        // Deterministic startup guarantee: if ATR is unavailable (na,
        // e.g. during warm-up before atrLength bars exist), fall back
        // to the Fixed threshold rather than producing an undefined
        // or overly permissive comparison.
        threshold := na(currentATR) ? minimumLegPoints : math.max(minimumLegPoints, currentATR * atrMultiplier)
    else
        // THRESHOLD_FIXED (default) - identical to pre-Sprint-2.2 behaviour.
        threshold := minimumLegPoints

    threshold

passesMinimumLegFilter(float transitionSwingPrice) =>
    [_, _, lastConfirmedPrice, _, hasConfirmedSwing] = getLastConfirmedSwing()
    bool passesFilter = true

    if hasConfirmedSwing
        float distanceFromLastConfirmed = legDistance(transitionSwingPrice, lastConfirmedPrice)
        float activeThreshold = resolveMinimumLegThreshold()
        passesFilter := distanceFromLastConfirmed >= activeThreshold

    passesFilter

//====================================================================
// REPLACEMENT ENGINE
//====================================================================

var int activePendingSwingType = SWING_NONE
var int activePendingSwingId = NO_SWING_ID
var int activePendingHighSwingId = NO_SWING_ID
var int activePendingLowSwingId = NO_SWING_ID
var int activeTransitionSwingId = NO_SWING_ID

var array<int> currentEventTypes = array.new_int()
var array<int> currentEventSwingTypes = array.new_int()
var array<int> currentEventSwingIds = array.new_int()
var array<float> currentEventPrices = array.new_float()
var array<int> currentEventBars = array.new_int()

var array<int> currentConfirmedSwingTypes = array.new_int()
var array<int> currentConfirmedSwingIds = array.new_int()
var array<float> currentConfirmedSwingPrices = array.new_float()
var array<int> currentConfirmedSwingBars = array.new_int()

resetCurrentBarEvents() =>
    array.clear(currentEventTypes)
    array.clear(currentEventSwingTypes)
    array.clear(currentEventSwingIds)
    array.clear(currentEventPrices)
    array.clear(currentEventBars)
    array.clear(currentConfirmedSwingTypes)
    array.clear(currentConfirmedSwingIds)
    array.clear(currentConfirmedSwingPrices)
    array.clear(currentConfirmedSwingBars)

recordCandidateEvent(int eventType, int swingType, int swingId, float swingPrice, int swingBar) =>
    array.push(currentEventTypes, eventType)
    array.push(currentEventSwingTypes, swingType)
    array.push(currentEventSwingIds, swingId)
    array.push(currentEventPrices, swingPrice)
    array.push(currentEventBars, swingBar)

recordConfirmedSwingEvent(int swingType, int swingId, float swingPrice, int swingBar) =>
    array.push(currentConfirmedSwingTypes, swingType)
    array.push(currentConfirmedSwingIds, swingId)
    array.push(currentConfirmedSwingPrices, swingPrice)
    array.push(currentConfirmedSwingBars, swingBar)

isBetterReplacement(int swingType, float candidatePrice, float activePrice) =>
    swingType == SWING_HIGH ? candidatePrice > activePrice : candidatePrice < activePrice

activateNewPendingSwing(int candidateType, float candidatePrice, int candidateBar, int swingId) =>
    int newSwingId = startPendingSwing(swingId, candidateType, candidatePrice, candidateBar)
    int updatedHighSwingId = candidateType == SWING_HIGH ? newSwingId : activePendingHighSwingId
    int updatedLowSwingId = candidateType == SWING_LOW ? newSwingId : activePendingLowSwingId

    recordCandidateEvent(EVENT_ACCEPTED, candidateType, newSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

    [candidateType, newSwingId, updatedHighSwingId, updatedLowSwingId]

processSameSideCandidate(int candidateType, float candidatePrice, int candidateBar) =>
    [_, storedPrice, _, _, exists] = getActiveSwing(activePendingSwingId)
    [transitionType, transitionPrice, transitionBar, _, transitionExists] = getSwing(activeTransitionSwingId)

    int updatedActiveType = activePendingSwingType
    int updatedActiveId = activePendingSwingId
    int updatedHighId = activePendingHighSwingId
    int updatedLowId = activePendingLowSwingId
    int updatedTransitionId = activeTransitionSwingId
    bool createdSwingRecord = false

    bool shouldReplace = exists and isBetterReplacement(candidateType, candidatePrice, storedPrice)
    int eventType = shouldReplace ? EVENT_REPLACED : EVENT_REJECTED

    if shouldReplace
        replacePendingSwing(activePendingSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

        if transitionExists and transitionBar <= candidateBar
            archivePendingSwing(activeTransitionSwingId)
            updatedTransitionId := NO_SWING_ID
        else if transitionExists and passesMinimumLegFilter(transitionPrice)
            // Sprint 2.3 (Revision 3 ordering fix): capture the previous
            // confirmed swing's reference BEFORE confirmPendingSwing()
            // flips this swing's own status to CONFIRMED. Calling
            // getLastConfirmedSwing() after that flip would incorrectly
            // return this swing itself as "the previous confirmed swing."
            [_, _, prevConfirmedPrice, prevConfirmedBar, prevConfirmedExists] = getLastConfirmedSwing()
            bool confirmed = confirmPendingSwing(activePendingSwingId)

            if confirmed
                // Sprint 2.3: confirmation-time metadata now goes through
                // the single finalizeConfirmedSwing() extension point
                // (relocated from an inline setSwingATR() call here in
                // Sprint 2.2 - same field, same timing, same value).
                // Patch 4: finalizeConfirmedSwing() now also computes
                // and writes swingStrength, using the previous-confirmed
                // reference captured above.
                finalizeConfirmedSwing(activePendingSwingId, currentATR, prevConfirmedPrice, prevConfirmedBar, prevConfirmedExists)
                recordConfirmedSwingEvent(candidateType, activePendingSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

            updatedActiveType := transitionType
            updatedActiveId := activeTransitionSwingId
            updatedHighId := transitionType == SWING_HIGH ? activeTransitionSwingId : activePendingHighSwingId
            updatedLowId := transitionType == SWING_LOW ? activeTransitionSwingId : activePendingLowSwingId
            updatedTransitionId := NO_SWING_ID
    else
        rejectPendingSwing(activePendingSwingId)

    recordCandidateEvent(eventType, candidateType, activePendingSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

    [updatedActiveType, updatedActiveId, updatedHighId, updatedLowId, updatedTransitionId, createdSwingRecord]

processOppositeCandidate(int candidateType, float candidatePrice, int candidateBar, int swingId) =>
    [storedType, storedPrice, storedBar, _, exists] = getActiveSwing(activePendingSwingId)
    [transitionType, transitionPrice, transitionBar, _, transitionExists] = getSwing(activeTransitionSwingId)

    int updatedActiveType = activePendingSwingType
    int updatedActiveId = activePendingSwingId
    int updatedHighId = activePendingHighSwingId
    int updatedLowId = activePendingLowSwingId
    int updatedTransitionId = activeTransitionSwingId
    bool createdSwingRecord = false

    int eventType = EVENT_ACCEPTED
    int eventSwingId = swingId

    bool transitionMatchesCandidate = transitionExists and transitionType == candidateType

    if not transitionMatchesCandidate
        if transitionExists
            archivePendingSwing(activeTransitionSwingId)

        int newTransitionId = startPendingSwing(swingId, candidateType, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

        updatedTransitionId := newTransitionId
        transitionType := candidateType
        transitionPrice := candidatePrice
        transitionBar := candidateBar
        transitionExists := true

        eventType := EVENT_ACCEPTED
        eventSwingId := newTransitionId
        createdSwingRecord := true
    else
        eventSwingId := activeTransitionSwingId

        if isBetterReplacement(candidateType, candidatePrice, transitionPrice)
            replacePendingSwing(activeTransitionSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

            transitionPrice := candidatePrice
            transitionBar := candidateBar
            eventType := EVENT_REPLACED
        else
            eventType := EVENT_REJECTED

    recordCandidateEvent(eventType, candidateType, eventSwingId, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

    bool canConfirmPendingSwing = exists and transitionExists and passesMinimumLegFilter(transitionPrice)

    if canConfirmPendingSwing
        // Sprint 2.3 (Revision 3 ordering fix): capture the previous
        // confirmed swing's reference BEFORE confirmPendingSwing() flips
        // this swing's own status to CONFIRMED - see identical rationale
        // in processSameSideCandidate() above.
        [_, _, prevConfirmedPrice, prevConfirmedBar, prevConfirmedExists] = getLastConfirmedSwing()
        bool confirmed = confirmPendingSwing(activePendingSwingId)

        if confirmed
            // Sprint 2.3: confirmation-time metadata now goes through
            // the single finalizeConfirmedSwing() extension point
            // (relocated from an inline setSwingATR() call here in
            // Sprint 2.2 - same field, same timing, same value).
            // Patch 4: finalizeConfirmedSwing() now also computes and
            // writes swingStrength, using the previous-confirmed
            // reference captured above.
            finalizeConfirmedSwing(activePendingSwingId, currentATR, prevConfirmedPrice, prevConfirmedBar, prevConfirmedExists)
            recordConfirmedSwingEvent(storedType, activePendingSwingId, storedPrice, storedBar)

        updatedActiveType := transitionType
        updatedActiveId := updatedTransitionId
        updatedHighId := transitionType == SWING_HIGH ? updatedTransitionId : activePendingHighSwingId
        updatedLowId := transitionType == SWING_LOW ? updatedTransitionId : activePendingLowSwingId
        updatedTransitionId := NO_SWING_ID

    [updatedActiveType, updatedActiveId, updatedHighId, updatedLowId, updatedTransitionId, createdSwingRecord]

processCandidate(int candidateType, float candidatePrice, int candidateBar, int swingId) =>
    int updatedActiveType = activePendingSwingType
    int updatedActiveId = activePendingSwingId
    int updatedHighId = activePendingHighSwingId
    int updatedLowId = activePendingLowSwingId
    int updatedTransitionId = activeTransitionSwingId
    bool createdSwingRecord = false

    if activePendingSwingType == SWING_NONE
        [firstType, firstId, firstHighId, firstLowId] = activateNewPendingSwing(candidateType, candidatePrice, candidateBar, swingId)

        updatedActiveType := firstType
        updatedActiveId := firstId
        updatedHighId := firstHighId
        updatedLowId := firstLowId
        updatedTransitionId := NO_SWING_ID
        createdSwingRecord := true

    else if activePendingSwingType == candidateType
        [sameType, sameId, sameHighId, sameLowId, sameTransitionId, sameCreated] = processSameSideCandidate(candidateType, candidatePrice, candidateBar)

        updatedActiveType := sameType
        updatedActiveId := sameId
        updatedHighId := sameHighId
        updatedLowId := sameLowId
        updatedTransitionId := sameTransitionId
        createdSwingRecord := sameCreated

    else
        [oppositeType, oppositeId, oppositeHighId, oppositeLowId, oppositeTransitionId, oppositeCreated] = processOppositeCandidate(candidateType, candidatePrice, candidateBar, swingId)

        updatedActiveType := oppositeType
        updatedActiveId := oppositeId
        updatedHighId := oppositeHighId
        updatedLowId := oppositeLowId
        updatedTransitionId := oppositeTransitionId
        createdSwingRecord := oppositeCreated

    validateDatabaseInDebug("Database integrity failed after candidate processing.")

    [updatedActiveType, updatedActiveId, updatedHighId, updatedLowId, updatedTransitionId, createdSwingRecord]

resetCurrentBarEvents()

if hasCandidateHigh
    [updatedTypeHigh, updatedIdHigh, updatedHighSwingIdHigh, updatedLowSwingIdHigh, updatedTransitionIdHigh, createdHighSwing] = processCandidate(SWING_HIGH, candidateHighPrice, candidateHighBar, nextSwingId)

    activePendingSwingType := updatedTypeHigh
    activePendingSwingId := updatedIdHigh
    activePendingHighSwingId := updatedHighSwingIdHigh
    activePendingLowSwingId := updatedLowSwingIdHigh
    activeTransitionSwingId := updatedTransitionIdHigh

    if createdHighSwing
        nextSwingId += 1

if hasCandidateLow
    [updatedTypeLow, updatedIdLow, updatedHighSwingIdLow, updatedLowSwingIdLow, updatedTransitionIdLow, createdLowSwing] = processCandidate(SWING_LOW, candidateLowPrice, candidateLowBar, nextSwingId)

    activePendingSwingType := updatedTypeLow
    activePendingSwingId := updatedIdLow
    activePendingHighSwingId := updatedHighSwingIdLow
    activePendingLowSwingId := updatedLowSwingIdLow
    activeTransitionSwingId := updatedTransitionIdLow

    if createdLowSwing
        nextSwingId += 1

